1 Model comparison

We compare three models:

  • Binomial (B)
  • Beta-Binomial (BB)
  • Zero-inflated Beta-Binomial (ZIBB)

See vignette ‘ModelOverview’ to inspect the different models.

Five genes for which the pairwise models inferred most discrepant usage coefficients are annotated.

4.1 Reality check

Given that zero-inflation does not play a large role in this dataset, we see no difference between the estimates produced by ZIBB and BB. On the other hand B is overconfident (narrow usage estimates) when there are few zeros among the other gene usages (IGHV1 and IGHV5).
